<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 7:56AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Patchy fog is impacting locations along interstate 15 between
Helena and Butte...
Patchy dense fog has developed in places in Jefferson County,
especially near Elk Park. Visibility may fall to as low as one
half mile at times. Motorists should be prepared for highly
variable visibility across short distances. Slow down, turn on low
beam headlights, and allow extra spacing between the vehicle in
front of you.
The fog is expected to dissipate by 10 AM MDT this morning.</description>
